careers.name: Crop, nursery,and greenhouse farmworkers and laborers
careers.description: Drive and control farm equipment to till soil and to plant, cultivate, and harvest crops. May perform tasks, such as crop baling or hay bucking. May operate stationary equipment to perform post-harvest tasks, such as husking, shelling, threshing, and ginning.
careers.classes: Agricultural Sciences, Agricultural Economics, Animal Science

careers.name: Natural science managers
careers.description: Plan, direct, or coordinate activities in such fields as life sciences, physical sciences, mathematics, statistics, and research and development in these fields.

careers.name: Landscaping and groundskeeping workers
careers.description: Landscape or maintain grounds of property using hand or power tools or equipment. Workers typically perform a variety of tasks, which may include any combination of the following: sod laying, mowing, trimming, planting, watering, fertilizing, digging, raking, sprinkler installation, and installation of mortarless segmental concrete masonry wall units.
careers.classes: Planting Design and Theory of Landscape Architecture

careers.name: Construction managers
careers.description: Plan, direct, or coordinate, usually through subordinate supervisory personnel, activities concerned with the construction and maintenance of structures, facilities, and systems. Participate in the conceptual development of a construction project and oversee its organization, scheduling, budgeting, and implementation. Includes managers in specialized construction fields, such as carpentry or plumbing.
careers.classes: Construction Scheduling, Construction Cost Estimating and Cost Control, and Construction Management

careers.name: Floral designers
careers.description: Design, cut, and arrange live, dried, or artificial flowers and foliage.
careers.celebrities: Pim van den Akker, Terence Conran
careers.classes: Flower Identification, History of Floral Design

careers.name: Art directors
careers.description: Formulate design concepts and presentation approaches for visual communications media, such as print, broadcasting, and advertising. Direct workers engaged in art work or layout design.
careers.classes: Psychology of Art and Creativity, Making Comics, and Photography Basics

careers.name: Stock clerks and orderfillers
careers.description: Coordinate and expedite the flow of work and materials within or between departments of an establishment according to production schedule. Duties include reviewing and distributing production, work, and shipment schedules; conferring with department supervisors to determine progress of work and completion dates; and compiling reports on progress of work, inventory levels, costs, and production problems.

careers.name: Chief executives
careers.description: Determine and formulate policies and provide overall direction of companies or private and public sector organizations within guidelines set up by a board of directors or similar governing body. Plan, direct, or coordinate operational activities at the highest level of management with the help of subordinate executives and staff managers.
careers.classes: Human Resources, Leadership and Management, and Entrepreneurship

careers.name: Teacher assistants
careers.description: Perform duties that are instructional in nature or deliver direct services to students or parents. Serve in a position for which a teacher has ultimate responsibility for the design and implementation of educational programs and services.

careers.name: Postsecondary teachers
careers.description: Unknown at this time

careers.name: Tellers
careers.description: Receive and pay out money. Keep records of money and negotiable instruments involved in a financial institution's various transactions.

careers.name: Financial managers
careers.description: Plan, direct, or coordinate accounting, investing, banking, insurance, securities, and other financial activities of a branch, office, or department of an establishment.

careers.name: Legislators
careers.description: Develop, introduce or enact laws and statutes at the local, tribal, State, or Federal level. Includes only workers in elected positions.

careers.name: Financial examiners
careers.description: Enforce or ensure compliance with laws and regulations governing financial and securities institutions and financial and real estate transactions. May examine, verify, or authenticate records.

careers.name: Home health aides
careers.description: Provide routine individualized healthcare such as changing bandages and dressing wounds, and applying topical medications to the elderly, convalescents, or persons with disabilities at the patient's home or in a care facility. Monitor or report changes in health status. May also provide personal care such as bathing, dressing, and grooming of patient.

careers.name: Surgeons
careers.description: Physicians who treat diseases, injuries, and deformities by invasive, minimally-invasive, or non-invasive surgical methods, such as using instruments, appliances, or by manual manipulation.

careers.name: Combined food preparation and serving workers
careers.description: Perform a variety of food preparation duties other than cooking, such as preparing cold foods and shellfish, slicing meat, and brewing coffee or tea.

careers.name: Gaming managers
careers.description: Plan, direct, or coordinate gaming operations in a casino. May formulate house rules.

careers.name: Shampooers
careers.description: Shampoo and rinse customers' hair.

careers.name: Industrial-organizational psychologists
careers.description: Apply principles of psychology to human resources, administration, management, sales, and marketing problems. Activities may include policy planning; employee testing and selection, training and development; and organizational development and analysis. May work with management to organize the work setting to improve worker productivity.

careers.name: Computer user support specialists
careers.description: Provide technical assistance to computer users. Answer questions or resolve computer problems for clients in person, or via telephone or electronically. May provide assistance concerning the use of computer hardware and software, including printing, installation, word processing, electronic mail, and operating systems.

careers.name: Systems software developers
careers.description: Develop, create, and modify general computer applications software or specialized utility programs. Analyze user needs and develop software solutions. Design software or customize software for client use with the aim of optimizing operational efficiency. May analyze and design databases within an application area, working individually or coordinating database development as part of a team. May supervise computer programmers.

Clusters.name: Law, public safety, corrections, and security

careers.name: Lifeguards, ski patrol, and other recreational protective service workers
careers.description: Monitor recreational areas, such as pools, beaches, or ski slopes to provide assistance and protection to participants.

careers.name: Judges, magistrate judges, and magistrates
careers.description: Arbitrate, advise, adjudicate, or administer justice in a court of law. May sentence defendant in criminal cases according to government statutes or sentencing guidelines. May determine liability of defendant in civil cases. May perform wedding ceremonies.

careers.name: Sewing machine operators
careers.description: Operate or tend sewing machines to join, reinforce, decorate, or perform related sewing operations in the manufacture of garment or nongarment products.

careers.name: Nuclear power reactor operators
careers.description: Operate or control nuclear reactors. Move control rods, start and stop equipment, monitor and adjust controls, and record data in logs. Implement emergency procedures when needed. May respond to abnormalities, determine cause, and recommend corrective action.

careers.name: Cashiers
careers.description: Receive and disburse money in establishments other than financial institutions. May use electronic scanners, cash registers, or related equipment. May process credit or debit card transactions and validate checks.

careers.name: Marketing managers
careers.description: Plan, direct, or coordinate marketing policies and programs, such as determining the demand for products and services offered by a firm and its competitors, and identify potential customers. Develop pricing strategies with the goal of maximizing the firm's profits or share of the market while ensuring the firm's customers are satisfied. Oversee product development or monitor trends that indicate the need for new products and services.

careers.name: Social science research assistants
careers.description: Plan, develop, or conduct surveys. May analyze and interpret the meaning of survey data, determine survey objectives, or suggest or test question wording. Includes social scientists who primarily design questionnaires or supervise survey teams.

careers.name: Petroleum engineers
careers.description: Devise methods to improve oil and gas extraction and production and determine the need for new or modified tool designs. Oversee drilling and offer technical advice.

careers.name: Parking Lot Attendant
careers.description: Park vehicles or issue tickets for customers in a parking lot or garage. May collect fee.

careers.name: Air Traffic Controller
careers.description: Control air traffic on and within vicinity of airport and movement of air traffic between altitude sectors and control centers according to established procedures and policies. Authorize, regulate, and control commercial airline flights according to government or company regulations to expedite and ensure flight safety.
